The 1999 İzmit earthquake (also known as the Kocaeli or Gölcük earthquake) occurred on 17 August at 3:01 a.m. local time in northwestern Turkey. The shock had a moment magnitude of 7.6 and a maximum Mercalli Intensity of IX (Violent). The event last…

İzmit

İzmit (Greek: Νικομήδεια, Nikomedeia) is a city in Turkey, the administrative center of the Kocaeli Province as well as the Metropolitan Municipality. It is located at the Gulf of İzmit (the ancient Gulf of Astacus) in the Sea of Marmara, about 100 …

Kocaeli Province

Körfez, Kocaeli

Körfez is a town and district of the Kocaeli Province in the Marmara region of Turkey. The mayor is Yunus Pehlivan (AKP). It was created from eastern part of Gebze and western part of İzmit (Then called Center) districts in 1987. It has borders with…

Gölcük Naval Base

Gölcük Naval Base (Turkish: Gölcük Deniz Ana Üssü) is the main base of the Turkish Navy on the east coast of the Sea of Marmara in Gölcük, Kocaeli.
